			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">OK, the reason of the bug is that gdb gets control on SEGV by default (this can be changed by gdb command, but for all SEGVs, which is not what we want - we want to ignore just this particular SEGV).

If no other way to test data execution, this issue becomes a documentation issue - we have to explain the situation explicitly and clearly to our future gdb users, so they are not confused with this SEGV.

